...
21:37:23.239534[I] bootstrap data fetched now initializing shards with series blocks [{namespace metrics} {numShards 256} {numSeries 0}]
21:37:23.240778[I] bootstrap finished [{namespace metrics} {duration 23.325194ms}]
21:37:23.240856[I] bootstrapped
21:37:29.733025[I] successfully updated topology to 3 hosts  You can now write and read metrics using the API on the db nodes:  $ kubectl -n m3db port-forward svc/m3dbnode 9003
Forwarding from 127.0.0.1:9003 -  9003
Forwarding from [::1]:9003 -  9003  curl -sSf -X POST localhost:9003/writetagged -d '{
   namespace :  default ,
   id :  foo ,
   tags : [
    {
       name :  city ,
       value :  new_york 
    },
    {
       name :  endpoint ,
       value :  /request 
    }
  ],
   datapoint : {
     timestamp : ' $(date  +%s ) ',
     value : 42.123456789
  }
}'  $ curl -sSf -X POST http://localhost:9003/query -d '{
